"There is nothing to be gained by pretending that academic involvement is necessary, or even always desirable, in the quest for truth and knowledge.\n\n- Christopher\n|\nInvesting is like Yoga. Body, mind and soul have to be aligned.\n\n- Vijay\n|\nIf you stop learning, you soon forget what you already know.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nFor lack of knowledge of the Holy One, we perish in sin of hell.\n\n- Lailah Gifty, Akita\n|\nMost people who were educated have become the 'problems' instead of problem solvers.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Leaders' Frontpage: Leadership Insights from 21 Martin Luther King Jr. Thoughts\n|\nComplete freedom is as much curse as boon; freedom within strict and well-defined confines is, to me, ideal.\n\n- David Byrne, How Music Works\n|\nIf you haven't cried at least once while writing a chapter of your inspirational book, then you have to ask yourself if your're writing fiction.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nIf you read proverbs, you will find answers to every puzzle.\n\n- Lailah\n|\n[Christ] will come again. But we must look to Scripture, not human thought, for our guide to preparing.\n\n- David Jeremiah, Until Christ Returns: Living Faithfully Today While We Wait for Our Glorious Tomorrow\n|\nmerindukanmu adalah indahnya rasa, yang sukar kusembunyikan keresahannya\n\n- Rian Prasetia, @sekadar_coretan\n|\nAllegra's Austen wrote about the impact of financial need on the intimate lives of women. If she'd worked in a bookstore, Allegra would have shelved Austen in the horror section.\n\n- Karen Joy Fowler, The Jane Austen Book Club\n|\nThe secret to life is to live as though you know the secret.' Barbara Botch\n\n- Barbara Botch, Poet's Crossing\n|\nYou have to go head, even if no one goes with you.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nThe future will be what it will, and fretting about it will only make your fears more likely to come true.\n\n- Christopher Paolini, Inheritance\n|\nПлътта, ако крепне, крепне за сметка на духа; и духът, ако съзрява, то ене по друг начин, а за сметка на упокояването на плътта.\n\n- Феофан Затворник, Путь ко спасению. Краткий очерк аскетики.\n|\nWe never know the quality of someone else's life, though we seldom resist the temptation to assume and pass judgement.\n\n- Tami Hoag, Dark Horse\n|\nThe difference between school and life? In school, you're taught a lesson and then given a test. In life, you're given a test that teaches you a lesson.\n\n- Tom\n|\nQuoting son, Noah Levine: Once you see what the heart really needs, it doesn’t matter if you’re going to live or die, the work is always the same. (25)\n\n- Stephen Levine, A Year to Live: How to Live This Year as If It Were Your Last\n|\nLife is hell, at some point we all just have to get used to it.\n\n- Alysha Speer, Sharden\n|\nThe freer a society is, the more it leaves the family alone.\n\n- Peter Hitchens, The Abolition of Britain: From Winston Churchill to Princess Diana\n|\nNobody seems to understand that in such matters the tact and sympathy should come from the one who is about to die, not the poor bugger who has to take the news.\n\n- Stephen Fry, The Hippopotamus\n|\nThis life is not perfect, live it to the full, it's all we have\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, Pearls Of Eternity\n|\nL'essere notata non mi va a genio, questo mi pare chiaro.\n\n- Sara Dardikh, Baci nell'ombra\n|\nWhen people wind you up, just remind them what happens to a piece of elastic.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nIf everyone bows in front of your wisdom, your greatest wisdom will be to tell them not to bow!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\n[P]oetry resembles metaphysics: one does not mind one's own, but one does not like anyone else's.\n\n- Samuel\n|\nhope for the best, prepare for the worst\n\n- Chris Bradford, The Ring of Earth\n|\nTell me what you want, and I'll tell you who you think you are. Tell me what you fear, and I'll tell you who you really are.\n\n- Brunonia Barry, The Fifth Petal\n|\nOne of the most terrifying things I fear is not my potential, but how much regret I’ll die with should I never use it.\n\n- Craig\n|\nOh Julie, wouldn’t I know if you were dead? Wouldn’t I feel it happening, like a jolt of electricity to my heart?\n\n- Elizabeth Wein, Code Name Verity\n|\nMost important thing in life is family,Without them you are nothing.Whatever you do will be worth nothing,If there is no one to appreciate it.\n\n- Akash Lakhotia, World Hypnotized: Making of the Fuhrer\n|\nMy heart has joined the Thousand, for my friend stopped running today.\n\n- Richard Adams, Watership Down\n|\nThere is no eleventh hour with Cosmic Ordering, only the golden hour.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Cosmic Ordering Guide\n|\nAll that I hope to say in books, all that I ever hope to say, is that I love the world.\n\n- E.B.\n|\nThe past is a place of learning, not a place of living.\n\n- Roy\n|\nThe way to my heart shattered when you left me, but I was glad because your memories were invulnerable, locked inside my heart.\n\n- Anmol Rawat, A Little Chorus of Love\n|\nThere's no retirement for an artist,its your way of living so theres no end to it.\n\n- Bono\n|\nI jump for joy every day. My body pulses with joy, and my vibration soars. I feel amazing.\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, Joyful Living: 101 Ways to Transform Your Spirit and Revitalize Your Life\n|\nThat's what life is all about - you're busy, I'm busy, and the end result is death. Sooner or later, that's what it comes to. ('The Death Of Wang Asao')\n\n- Xiao Hong, Selected Stories Of Xiao Hong\n|\nAs I contemplate a relationship with God, I find that I’m afraid to ride on the coattails of the infinite. But what I fear more than that is spending my life in the coat closet.\n\n- Craig\n|\nIt may seem that you are on the path alone, but the light that guides you is coming from somewhere. Trust your every step because none of us walk this journey alone.\n\n- Toni\n|\nIn crime and enmity they lie Who sin and tell us love can die, Who say to us in slander's breath That love belongs to sin and death.\n\n- John Clare, Poems Chiefly from Manuscript\n|\nOh,' she said, in a very different way. 'Well. Thanks for my part in the compliment. Naturally I'd love to be watched and controlled, but I think I may be washing my hair that day.\n\n- Sarah Rees Brennan, The Demon's Covenant\n|\nSilver surfers ... nah, that's old hat. Retire a gold surfer with Cosmic Ordering.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Cosmic Ordering: You can be successful\n|\nThis time will never come again in your life. Enjoy every moment, right now, before the time is gone.\n\n- Avina\n|\nBetsy returned to her chair, took off her coat and hat, opened her book and forgot the world again.\n\n- Maud Hart Lovelace, Betsy and Tacy Go Downtown\n|\nSomething is wrong with me, it's something about me. it has to be me because all those people cannot have changed.\n\n- Harper Lee, Go Set a Watchman\n|\nContrary to your beliefs, I am stronger then what you give me credit for, but the real lesson here is the knowledge to know I don't owe you an explanation to anything.\n\n- Nikki\n|\nInstead of you to be at the mercy of whatever they have made you into, rebuild your life into what it should be.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nIn my pursuit of historical ecology, I find the pleasure of reading history.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nI work backwards with the ending in mind as I create art, stories, poems and books. Always in a process of becoming.\n\n- Jill\n|\nDo not do what you cannot continue to deliver.For, remember, the world wants to see a continuity of delivery of set standards...!\n\n- Sujit Lalwani, Life Simplified!\n|\nYour love was a vine - enchanting and beautiful, crawling around my heart and up my throat; then it strangled me. Your love, hauntingly tragic.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nI've tried that love thing for the last time. My heart says no, no! Nobody's supposed to be here, but you came along and changed my mind\n\n- Deborah\n|\nLips may lie, but the heart always tells the truth.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nMen occasionally stumble over the truth, but most of them pick themselves up and hurry off as if nothing ever happened.\n\n- Winston\n|\nThe truth is the last thing that matters,' she said. 'And you can believe one thing of the truth and me: I keep it well hidden, inside my heart.\n\n- Philippa Gregory, The Virgin's Lover\n|\nThe more knowledge that distributed, the more people know, so the more worthless that knowledge.\n\n- Danny\n|\nEvery scene should be able to answer three questions: 'Who wants what from whom? What happens if they don't get it? Why now?\n\n- David Mamet, Bambi vs. Godzilla: On the Nature, Purpose, and Practice of the Movie Business\n|\nBe like Jesus. Live love, speak love, think love…..do all things in love.\n\n- Omoakhuana\n|\nLearn to drive?''Never,' said Quentin. 'My mission in life is to be a passenger.\n\n- Diana Wynne Jones, Archer's Goon\n|\nWhen you are ready to accept the risk, only then can you open the doors of opportunity\n\n- Debasish\n|\nDon't think about making life better for other people who don't even deserve you, rather, focus on making your life the best, for yourself and those who love you.\n\n- C.\n|\nDon't give in to your fears. If you do, you won't be able to talk to your heart.\n\n- Paulo Coelho, The Alchemist\n|\nLet your Creed be to do a Good Deed. When your Focus is on your Need instead of your Greed, you will succeed.\n\n- RVM\n|\nDivinity is born from neural processes, not some Supreme Entity.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Autobiography of God: Biopsy of A Cognitive Reality\n|\nWhat a kid I got, I told him about the birds and the bees and he told me about the butcher and my wife.\n\n- Rodney\n|\nYou couldn't be romantic if your life depended on it.' 'You know what's lucky? Most bad guys don't ask you to be romantic on command, so that probably won't matter.\n\n- Rachel Caine, Kiss of Death\n|\nIf he was not exactly a Spartan, he was, you might say, spartanatical. Things happened to you; they were good,or they were bad - and that was the truth about everything.\n\n- A.E. Coppard, Dusky Ruth: And Other Stories\n|\nAs much as we thirst for approval, we dread condemnation.\n\n- Hans\n|\nEvery page should explode, either because of its staggering absurdity, the enthusiasm of its principles, or its typography.\n\n- Tristan Tzara, Manifesti del dadaismo\n|\nLife is not a dress rehearsal. Finding love is all about taking a risk, taking control of your social life, and knowing that you won't waste today because tomorrow is a gift.\n\n- Fran\n|\nEverything I've ever done, in the writing world, has been to expand articulation, rather than to close it.\n\n- Toni\n|\nAnymore, no one's mind is their own.\n\n- Chuck Palahniuk, Lullaby\n|\nPeople, who do so little for you, always try to ruin your life\n\n- Sami\n|\nThe same styles you used earlier may become monotonous over time. You want to remain relevant, so you got to change that style. Reinvent yourself always: You must create a new you\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Leaders' Frontpage: Leadership Insights from 21 Martin Luther King Jr. Thoughts\n|\nDifferent languages, the same thoughts; servant to thoughts and their masters.\n\n- Dejan Stojanovic, The Sun Watches the Sun\n|\nLove in your mind can be felt by some, love in your heart can be felt by many, but love in your soul can be felt by all.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nWe all get lots of people. And maybe we don’t always get to have them the exact way we want them, but if we can figure out a way to compromise, you know, then we can keep them all.\n\n- John Corey Whaley, Noggin\n|\nI can't make out what they're saying; it sounds like: hiss, blah, she hiss, squeak. But the aunt appears to speak the native language.\n\n- Emma Chase, Sustained\n|\nFaith moves mountains, but only knowledge moves them to the right place...\n\n- Joseph\n|\nA good book isn't written, it's rewritten.\n\n- Phyllis A. Whitney, Guide to Fiction Writing\n|\nIn politics, stupidity is not a handicap.\n\n- Napoléon\n|\nEverybody was dying, or already dead, or leaving other people, and the year was dying into winter, and the only thing to do was make some noise.\n\n- Marina Endicott, Good to a Fault\n|\nSoap, toothpaste and detergent are all 'new and improved'. Are you?\n\n- Diana Dentinger, Modus Vivendi: Your Life Your Way\n|\nHow exquisitely human was the wish for permanent happiness, and how thin human imagination became trying to achieve it.\n\n- Toni Morrison, Paradise\n|\nFor an adventurous life, seek not security. Dance with uncertainty to create magnificence and beauty.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nTo the well-organized mind, death is but the next great adventure.\n\n- J.K. Rowling, Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone\n|\nTime is precious, but truth is more precious than time.\n\n- Benjamin\n|\nNever rebel for the sake of rebelling, but always rebel for the sake of truth.\n\n- Criss Jami, Killosophy\n|\nThis life’s hard, but it’s harder if you’re stupid.\n\n- George V. Higgins, The Friends of Eddie Coyle\n|\nWhen you showed someone how you felt, it was fresh and honest. When you told someone how you felt, there might be nothing behind the words but habit or expectation.\n\n- Jodi Picoult, Handle with Care\n|\nCome to think of it, maybe God is a He after all, because only a cruel force would create something this beautiful and make it inaccessible to most people.\n\n- Raquel Cepeda, Bird of Paradise: How I Became Latina\n|\nIf obstacles are large, jump higher.\n\n- Steve Backley, The Champion in all of Us: 12 Rules for Success\n|\nGenius is one percent inspiration, ninety-nine percent perspiration.\n\n- Thomas\n|\nIf people institute wrong institutions, wrong institutions do not just produce wrong people, but wrong people who understand and accept mediocrity as an institution\n\n- Ernest\n|\nFreedom, one of the most important words in any language.\n\n- Anwar\n|\nThe secret of happiness is freedom, the secret of freedom is courage.\n\n- Carrie Jones, Need\n|\nThere is a difference between how you live your life, and what you do with your life.\n\n- Abhijit\n|\nMany people can and have written books, but many have nothing to say.\n\n- Amy"